ting recent paper:\n\"Initial pulse of Siberian Traps sills as the trigger of the end-Permian mass extinction\" - Burgess et al, 2017\nThere's also\n\"Catastrophic dispersion of coal fly ash into oceans during the latest Permian extinction\" - Grasby et al, 2011.", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "113010229", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "the concentration of co2 in the air has increased by 40 % since the start of the industrial revolution", "effect": "the climate is changing this time"}, {"cause": "astronomical cycles increased the insolation affecting the earth", "effect": "the last glacial stage ended"}, {"cause": "first warming", "effect": "co2 to come out of the oceans which boosted the warming"}]}, {"id": "113086381", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520195840000}, "author": "loco_p_man", "author_id": "13126382", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nWind energy is currently producing about 1/4 of our energy.\nBQEND\nTT, I know you are a stickler for facts and precision. So you will not object when I correct your comment to\nWind energy is currently producing about 1/4 of our electricity.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "113034398", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113086242", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520195629000}, "author": "loco_p_man", "author_id": "13126382", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nthe US is not part of the Paris Agreement\nBQEND\nBernie, try to get your facts right. \nJust as there is a process to accede to the Paris Agreement, there is a process to withdraw. And that process has a timetable. The United States cannot officially announce its plan to withdraw from the agreement until November 4, 2019. At that time, if Donald Trump is still president and hasn\u2019t changed his mind, he can send a letter to the U.N. secretary general notifying the organization of America\u2019s intent to leave. There is a one-year waiting period before that withdrawal takes effect, 