ned and explained explicitly.\nBQEND\ni.e. A feedback that reduces an initial warming is a \"negative feedback.\", yet the study you refer to suggests that it may have greater role in Arctic amplified warming and hence a positive feedback.\nyou really haven't a clue what you were posting and why.", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "113024586", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113025274", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520081245000}, "author": "KurtinSwitzerland", "author_id": "16112781", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "No, Dennis - read the link to the article on arctic amplification. It is a characteristic, quite independent of [human] CO2 emissions.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "113024761", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113025209", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520081160000}, "author": "KurtinSwitzerland", "author_id": "16112781", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Pretzel,\nThe article claims, \nBQSTART\n\"... climate change on the scale now under way is outside all previous experience of which we have records.\"\nBQEND\nYet I would think that careful observers of climate proxies might beg to differ.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "113022375", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113025014", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520080886000}, "author": "richjenn14", "author_id": "10003949", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"This wouldn't have anything to do with the inconvenient fact that global temperatures have been in a tailspin since 2016, would it?\"\nThis link leads us to a site on which the Author says \"it now seems clear to me that CO2 is indeed the primary driver of global warming, which is proceeding at roughly 1.5\u00b0C per century\"and\"as a life-long Green I think a shift to a efficient and sustainable way of life is a Good Thing in any case, and I'd invite my fellow engineers to use their energies to help solve our many inefficiencies\"\nSo what the **