 is there available? Some food for thought.The energy density of Uranium through a fission breeder reactor is.........80,620,000 MJ/Kg(80 million six hundred and twenty thousand MegaJoules per kilogram)So we could just go on poisoning the world with rubbish out of wood or ......follow a sensible policy of area appropriate renewables and nuclear power as advocated by world renowned climate scientists and the IPCC.https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2015/dec/03/nuclear-power-paves-the-only-viable-path-forward-on-climate-change", "recommendation_count": "2", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112989542", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520008687000}, "author": "Mary1952", "author_id": "18404292", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "yes, agreed but the new trees cannot possiby do this fast enough - that's important - burning is rapid but new trees take time to grow .... and even then what about the fine particle pollution? You or someone else here says the power plants use the latest technology that doesn't pollute (or hardly - particulates, I mean) but can we really beleive that? if domestic and institutional stoves are anything to go by, no ....", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "112966401", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112989365", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520008541000}, "author": "Mary1952", "author_id": "18404292", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "interesting - thanks", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "112970289", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113004424", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520028195000}, "author": "retirednow", "author_id": "12832182", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Nice try, fail. Anyone who says they lived with all those issues for 16 years would not be able to understand the science of any topic.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "112968721", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112989162", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520008380000}, "author": "Mary