h system models.\nWhat is clear is burning would can be carbon-neutral, while burning fossil fuels can't be (unless the rate you burn them is as low at the rate that trees get turned into fossil fuels, which is very small).\n(Note this is a different question than the particulate & other crud you get from burning wood domestically.)", "recommendation_count": "1", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112961865", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1519987087000}, "author": "Mary1952", "author_id": "18404292", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Yes - and see John Beddington's work too.And Stephen Holgate's on the health side. Wood smoke particles are very unhealthy.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "112944646", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112971403", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1519995386000}, "author": "IainCogs", "author_id": "11150095", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Do the maths for whole populations of trees rather than individuals. #NotSeeingTheWoodForTheTrees", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "112949762", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112961704", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1519986942000}, "author": "Mary1952", "author_id": "18404292", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "See what John Beddington has to say on this topic?", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "112944857", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112961576", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1519986850000}, "author": "Mary1952", "author_id": "18404292", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Nellie?", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "112945649", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "112971370", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1519995353000}, "author": "ScottishScientist1", "author_id": "14857627", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nand politicians can make good and bad decisions alike\nBQENDReally? Can you name even one single UK politician who has taken the good decision 