oast of Ellsemere Island, which are made of super- thickened landfast ice supported by pack ice in the adjacent Arctic Ocean. These ice shelves have been stable for most of the last 5.5 kyr based on driftwood ages (England et al., 2008), but declined by more than 90% during the 20th century and continue to break at a notable rate (Mueller et al., 2008).\nBQEND\nBQSTART\nthe accelerated ice loss during the last several decades lead to conditions not documented in at least the last few thousand years.\nBQEND", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "113445357", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "all", "effect": "the same conclusion that current sea ice is lower than any time in the past few thousand years"}, {"cause": "the orbitally- driven decreasing summer insolation with the positive feedbacks from ice and snow albedo", "effect": "that"}, {"cause": "bqend bqstart the accelerated ice loss during the last several decades", "effect": "conditions not documented in at least the last few thousand years"}]}, {"id": "113455019", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520901429000}, "author": "Tony B", "author_id": "13732825", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"Then they wonder why the guardian opens fewer & fewer articles for comment.\"\nWhen it comes to climate science, the comments based on scientific reason explaining why AGW is a problem are drowned out by the largely scientifically ignorant denislist claims.\nScientific enquiry is the only valid mechanism for evaluating whether climate change is happening.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "113434648", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113457130", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520908074000}, "author": "ID9766495", "author_id": "3333597", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "The two are not mutually exclusive.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "113456748", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113457117", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1520908008000}, "author": "ID9766495", "au