ecause a beetle wing-case is usually sufficient to identify a species, and the species have not changed much in a long time.\nAny given collection of species taken together indicates a very precise temperature.\nHis discovery tells us that the Earth's climates are not necessarily stable.\nThese rapid climate events were confirmed a few decades later by ice cores from the Greenland ice sheet..... the events he discovered had a number of natural causes.\nNot long before he died in 2011, he said that people are messing with a trigger that causes climate change, and the consequences are likely to be 'ferocious'.\n'Ferocious' is a difficult word to forget.", "recommendation_count": "9", "in_reply_to": "113647222", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "a beetle wing case is usually sufficient to identify a species", "effect": "the process works and the species have not changed much in a long time"}, {"cause": "that", "effect": "climate change"}]}, {"id": "113647529", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521225710000}, "author": "RJander", "author_id": "15758543", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "It appears he did not learn anything.", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "113646795", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113647517", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521225684000}, "author": "JulesBywaterLees", "author_id": "4738374", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nWhat makes you think that the earth's climate should be stable ?\nBQEND\nroughly about 5,000 years of stable climate and the point when humans switched from hunter gathers to agriculture.It is also a temperature range that suits growing grains- being a primary source of food either directly or as animal feed.We know the temperature has been mainly stable because plant life- our food, the trees we grow for buildings [and once for fuel] are very fussy- they are goldilocks.\nTo suggest otherwise is brazen presumptuousness - you offer nothing in any kind of argument that the plane