ed repeatedly. Therefore at the moment it has to be taken with a pinch of salt.\nBQSTART\nClimate science is a very complex science, a young science, and an important science.\nBQEND\nIncorrect.It is not a young science. The basic physics were established in the mid C19, and AGW was predicted by Arrhenius in 1896.\nIt is correct to say it is complex, and we are still advancing the scientific understanding.\nHowever, your argument boils down to \"we don't know everything, therefore we know nothing\". \nAll the variations you mentioned are relatively well know, it is clouds, and feedbacks that are the main area of research to nailing down TCS and ECS.\nBQSTART\nObscuring the science with political narratives does no one any favors.\nBQEND\nWhich is what the fossil fuel companies are actively doing, aided and abetted by ideological fellow travellers who spread FUD about the actual state of the science.\nAll the best.", "recommendation_count": "18", "in_reply_to": "114077285", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114083386", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522180039000}, "author": "KingInYellow", "author_id": "3917113", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nThe \"climate denial\" Nuccitelli characterizes as science denial is instead the well respected position that climate sensitivity is near the low end of the IPCC 1.5 to 4.5 range,\nBQEND\nIncorrect.Climate change denial (denial of AGW) has a continuum of positions which deniers can hold simultaneously:- there is no greenhouse affect- CO2 is not increasing- if it is then it is not from anthropogenic sources- if it is increasing, then it will have minimal affect- there is no increase in temperatures- if temperatures are increasing, it's a good thing- and if it isn't a good thing its too late anyway\nAny and all of those points can also be accompanied with outright accusations of fraud and manipulation as part of variously socialist plots, plans for personal monetary gain, and or collusion with vested