r than land-fill)\nFinally, ignore any idiot who tells you to stop using plastic items. They are almost always better for the environment that any alternative other than using nothing. Just be sure to recycle or throw in regular rubbish. Remember when someone tells you it is better to grow a bamboo tree half way around the world, bring it here, disinfect it, make a toothbrush from it varnish it then after a short life allow it to decompose into Climate changing gases, then they either don't understand the science or they plan to make some money out of it.", "recommendation_count": "0", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113927550", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521821358000}, "author": "SteveInLondon", "author_id": "2649173", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "And they'll thank you for it...", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "113924897", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113927544", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521821344000}, "author": "R Anon", "author_id": "17206208", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Technically, a scientific observation, that would be a benefit to the planet.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "113926443", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113924980", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521818243000}, "author": "MGLane", "author_id": "4132693", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Go Vegan! Don\u2019t use plastic. Simple, job done, problem solved... next", "recommendation_count": "4", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113924907", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521818163000}, "author": "RJander", "author_id": "15758543", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Don't use candles unless they are beeswax. Ordinary candles are made of petroleum. Better off using electric light. Just keep one light on so you don't bump into the furniture.", "recommendation_count": "5", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113927449", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521821240000}, "author": "R Ano