f phasing out fossil fuel technologies, banning exploration for new reserves, and setting maximum limits on emissions per kWh.\nBQEND\nThese ARE all market mechanisms. Let's look at the first as an example. Suppose we told the automotive industry that we were going to ban all ICEs by 2040 in the UK. Oh -\nwe've already done it. We've sent a signal to the market about how a whole industry has to behave - with a clear time limit. Suppose we said the same to homeowners : that all oil and gas heating would become illegal from 2040. That is a massive signal to the market for ASHPs, GSHPs and hydrogen heating that there will be a market for them.....anf they will invest accordingly.\nExactly the same principle would apply to your suggestions about banning exploration for new reserves, and setting maximum limits on emissions.\nI think you imagine there is some action that we can take that is nothing to do with markets..... there may be, but I can't think what it is.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "114175379", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114159804", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522332743000}, "author": "TigerRepellingRock", "author_id": "1859343", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nWe are installing a mix of renewables and nuclear because they complement each other and the UK public has bought into that.\nBQEND\nHaven't you heard? Its all\na conspiracy to secretly fund trident.\nAndy Stirling, still trying to make \"fetch\" happen. \nBQSTART\n\"So why does the UK debate on these issues remain so muted?\"\nBQEND (comments disabled)", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114154186", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "they complement each other and the uk public has bought into that", "effect": "we are installing a mix of renewables and nuclear"}]}, {"id": "114159670", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522332567000}, "author": "ColinG", "author_id": "2578657", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nbut the