 need to be made, on individual cases. Oil wells, refineries, open-caste mines, combustion engine pollution and, obviously, climate change itself are all damaging to wildlife in one way or another. Have you previously fretted about this? If not, why not? How far does your concern for tortoises actually go?I have yet to meet a genuine conservationist who is not deeply concerned about AGW and the need for urgent mitigation. I do, however, very often read posts claiming renewable power will be an ecological catastrophe from posters claims to be \"environmentalists\" who also inevitably claim AGW is fake science and who never, funnily enough, post on the issue of wildlife outside of this context. So yes, there will be bad effects from solar sites in some situations, although in others (as I said) they can be a positive local ecological improvement. The task is to address them and mitigate them as much as possible. Not to use it opportunistically as a mere stick to beat renewables with.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "114174688", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114157568", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522330235000}, "author": "TTauriStellarbody", "author_id": "16773618", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nCorrecting people about abbreviations (irrelevant) in a serious conversation.\nBQENDThis is not a serious conversation.\nIts a denier flapping for attention. HTH.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "114156364", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114157489", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522330153000}, "author": "TTauriStellarbody", "author_id": "16773618", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Thank you for taking the time to respond however I have zero interest in a discussion of such low quality on such a little read forum.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114156784", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114167861", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522344716000}, "author": "JulesBywaterLees", "a