o carbon, has a long lifespan and is easy on the eye. And, importantly, it is very British.\u201d\nThat\u2019s why Elborne\u2019s business has committed \u00a320 million ($25 million) to tidal power in the U.K. and will manufacture generators, transformers and electrical transmission equipment on the British Isles. It\u2019s also helping U.K. build the world\u2019s first power-generating tidal lagoon in Swansea Bay, off the coast of South Wales. The lagoon will cover over 4.2 square miles (11 square kilometers) \u2014 an area more than three times the size of New York\u2019s Central Park.'\nhttps://www.ge.com/reports/sea-green-power-beneath-waves-tidal-electricity-becoming-reality-off-coast-wales/", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114144881", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114149072", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522321028000}, "author": "JacopoManfredi", "author_id": "18130674", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "You are funny - pretending to be some sort of environmentalist and climate change advocate - a true strawman.Apparently, we should ignore that 81% of US energy consumption is derived from fossil fuels and concentrate on the 3.5% of electricity produced by wind, solar and bio along with subsidising luxury EV for those wealthy enough to purchase them.Apparently you seem to believe that as long as the well off don\u2019t have to contribute anything climate change can be averted.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114143630", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114163711", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522337696000}, "author": "Steve Jones", "author_id": "11108528", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Well, I'm ready to be corrected, but so far you haven't answered my point directly.It's not an affectation, my phone's just set to French.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114147540", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114148494", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522320360000}, "author": "Comfort