cost when supplying other properties nearby. In so doing they reduce the maximum demand on the distribution network which as it must be built to handle maximum demand is a major contributor to that 54%. Hence rooftop solar panels reduce the retail price of electricity to all consumers.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "114295265", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "domestic air conditioner use", "effect": "that occur during heatwaves"}, {"cause": "it is close to the southern ocean", "effect": "southern australia is a windy place"}, {"cause": "lack of water", "effect": "power stations have run into trouble in drought times"}]}, {"id": "114313103", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522764654000}, "author": "AvMichelCroz", "author_id": "13022945", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Shipbuilding has mostly gone to Korea, I believe. Cars to Europe. \nSuch sensitivity about your Chinese connections! Raw nerve?", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114307006", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114313040", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522764551000}, "author": "UnderminingOrthodoxy", "author_id": "3898891", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I highlighted two fundamental misconceptions in your diatribe.\nBQSTART\nWith respect there is no nonsense in recognising what history has consistently shown that so many scientific theories which are 'proven' [according to definition] then followed, only to be overturned later. Why do you have a problem with that. There are countless examples.\nBQEND\nRather than attempt to defend or correct either, you have simply introduced another\nabsurd excuse for the rejection of science.\nThe fact that some aspect of science has been wrong in the past does not justify the rejection of any current science.\nI'm talking about laws, derived from repeated observations, not theories.\nEven though the story goes that Einstein \"overturned\" Newton, Newton's laws still apply just as well as they ever di