 matching whatever the capacity factor is i.e. ~30%. Which obviously isn't enough decarbonisation. I would definitely be keeping an eye out for when this upcoming paper becomes public:\n\"Least cost final zero carbon mixes in my forthcoming study rarely close to 80% wind/solar.\"\nIt isn't incredulity on my part, simply non-facile rational analysis. I'm not wedded to technologies like nuclear, but some understanding of the technology involved in making electricity, with some economics added in (esp. game theory) and by eliminating the implausible options, you are generally left with tech like nuclear being indispensable to any workable solution.\nAs far as nuclear is concerned in Australia, there is minimal chance it will be adopted any time soon. But this ultimately means that failure to decarbonise in a meaningful way is most certainly an option here. I don't like that prospect, but it is what it is.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114230289", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114240385", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522579581000}, "author": "justdreamingguss", "author_id": "13984824", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Canavan says he is concerned about jobs, who would have thought that, especially when he says that it's been an honour to work for the coal industry. This bloke is either a complete Climate Change denier or a far right wing capitalist who has no concern for humanity and only works within Capitalist's economics. Rape and pillage for individuals profit and after the devastation is complete, move on to do it all again somewhere else.", "recommendation_count": "4", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114232434", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522561447000}, "author": "ThisLyingGovernment", "author_id": "14945925", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "What would you like? The Singapore Package? Or any 1 of the triple zero group?", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114221187", "causal_relations": 