meterisation), forward prediction ((= projection), history matching, 1D, 2D and 3D analytical (= \"toy\") models to refine parameters or to sense-check processes, fine-scale models which capture the small-scale physics to aid pseudoization or parameterisation, coarse models plugged into a well-pipework-market network (analogous to climate models with economics etc. bolted on).\nPerhaps you could start by learning about petroleum models because you won't be put off by \"trigger words\". \nHowever first you should learn the basics because without that models can lead you astray.\nI recommend Dake's The Practice of Reservoir Engineering. Only \u00a389 from Amazon. It's very well written for a textbook.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "113845314", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "you wo n't be put off by trigger words", "effect": "perhaps you could start by learning about petroleum models"}, {"cause": "without that models can lead you astray", "effect": "however first you should learn the basics"}]}, {"id": "113849085", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521654349000}, "author": "dave6723", "author_id": "18522661", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nWhat surprises me is the missing 3% - as I understand it\nBQEND\nBut you more than amply demonstrate in your posts that you don't understand much about pretty much anything.\nSo your lack of understanding is worth squat.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "113845314", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "113848942", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1521654117000}, "author": "dave6723", "author_id": "18522661", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nOne possible explanation is an error in the fundamental physics used by the climate models\nBQEND\nAnother possible explanation is that RSS (the actual satellite experts) are right in their treatment of the fiendishly-difficult-to-process satellite data and UAH are wrong. Given the incremental tweaks made by RSS, and the